From: OctaneOS Build Fix <noreply@octaneos>
Date: Sun, 11 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] CrashRecoveryContext: use initial-exec TLS for shared lib compat

The three thread_local variables in CrashRecoveryContext.cpp are compiled
with the default local-exec TLS model when built without -fPIC. When LLVM
then links them into libLLVM.so, the linker rejects the local-exec
R_X86_64_TPOFF32 relocation:

  relocation R_X86_64_TPOFF32 can not be used when making a shared object;
  local-exec is incompatible with -shared

Switch all three to initial-exec, which accesses TLS via the GOT and is
fully compatible with shared libraries that are not dlopen'd at runtime.
---
 lib/Support/CrashRecoveryContext.cpp | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lib/Support/CrashRecoveryContext.cpp b/lib/Support/CrashRecoveryContext.cpp
--- a/lib/Support/CrashRecoveryContext.cpp
+++ b/lib/Support/CrashRecoveryContext.cpp
@@ -24,1 +24,1 @@
-static LLVM_THREAD_LOCAL const CrashRecoveryContextImpl *CurrentContext;
+static LLVM_THREAD_LOCAL __attribute__((tls_model("initial-exec"))) const CrashRecoveryContextImpl *CurrentContext;
@@ -91,1 +91,1 @@
-static LLVM_THREAD_LOCAL const CrashRecoveryContext *IsRecoveringFromCrash;
+static LLVM_THREAD_LOCAL __attribute__((tls_model("initial-exec"))) const CrashRecoveryContext *IsRecoveringFromCrash;
@@ -310,1 +310,1 @@
-static LLVM_THREAD_LOCAL const void* sCurrentExceptionHandle;
+static LLVM_THREAD_LOCAL __attribute__((tls_model("initial-exec"))) const void* sCurrentExceptionHandle;
